     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.013"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>By default the package provides ``
      <Code xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn"
         id="ID.014"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>\qverb
      </Code>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>'' and 
      <Code xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn"
         id="ID.015"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>\fverb
      </Code>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> ready for use. We have added 
      <Code xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn"
         id="ID.016"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>\cverb
      </Code>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>.
     </text>
    </text-unit>
    <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.017"
       rolemaps-to="Part"
      >
     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.018"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Now code like 
      <Code xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn"
         id="ID.019"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>pdflatex␣myfile
      </Code>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> can be ``
      <Code xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn"
         id="ID.020"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>enter
      </Code>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>''ed in a simplified way. ``
      <Code xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn"
         id="ID.021"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>\DeleteShortVerb
      </Code>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>'' removes previously defined shorthands again: |see|?
     </text>
    </text-unit>
